optimistic /ˌɒptɪˈmɪstɪk/

1. ADJ Someone who is optimistic is hopeful about the future or the success of something in particular. 乐观主义的 

例： The president says she is optimistic that an agreement can be worked out soon. 总统说，她对很快能达成协议持乐观态度。 

2. optimistically ADV 乐观主义地 [ADV with v] 

例： Both sides have spoken optimistically about the talks. 双方都对本次会谈表示乐观。

